sinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fprivate-equity-firms-consider-buying-out-peloton-cnbc-1033340322%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivate-equity%20sharks%20are%20reportedly%20circling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fpton-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estock%20is%20near%20record%20lows%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Peloton%20isn't%20going%20under%20imminently%2C%20but%20let's%20be%20real%20here%3A%20No%20fitness%20fad%20lasts%20forever.%20At%20least%20culturally%2C%20the%20Peloton%20graveyard%20is%20probably%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20right%20next%20to%20the%20Tae%20Bo%20cemetery%20and%20ThighMaster%20crematorium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeloton%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20pandemic%20Cinderella%20story.%20The%20company%20launched%20in%202012%20and%20started%20shipping%20bikes%20in%202014%2C%20but%20for%20much%20of%20its%20history%2C%20it%20operated%20as%20the%20creator%20of%20a%20product%20designed%20for%20a%20certain%20type%20of%20well-off%20fitness%20nut.%20Its%20initial%20equipment%20wasn't%20great%2C%20and%20it%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20finding%20investors.%20Eventually%2C%20it%20took%20off.%20It%20went%20public%20in%20September%202019%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20year%20it%20did%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-holiday-commercial-is-sparking-hate-confusion-from-watchers-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviral%20holiday%20ad%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20that%20pained-looking%20woman%20who%20gets%20a%20Peloton%20from%20who%20we%20can%20assume%20is%20her%20not-so-great%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20COVID-19%20hit%20in%202020%20and%20gyms%20shut%20down%2C%20demand%20for%20its%20products%20skyrocketed.%20Customers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-customers-complain-delays-cancellations-during-lockdown-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplained%20of%20monthslong%20wait%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20their%20bikes%20and%20treadmills%2C%20and%20Peloton%20scrambled%20to%20get%20its%20supply%20chain%20in%20order.%20Despite%20the%20pain%20points%2C%20times%20were%20pretty%20decent%3A%20Peloton%20booked%20its%20first%20%241%20billion%20in%20quarterly%20sales%20in%20the%20last%20three%20months%20of%202020%2C%20and%20its%20market%20cap%20peaked%20at%20about%20%2450%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20goes%20up%20often%20comes%20down%2C%20and%20in%20Peloton's%20case%2C%20the%20comedown%20was%20hard.%20While%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20that%20went%20wrong%2C%20the%20long%20and%20short%20of%20it%20is%20that%20Peloton%20failed%20to%20read%20the%20room%20on%20its%20pandemic%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20narrative%20and%20hype%20overshadowed%20its%20actual%20market%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rina%20Raphael%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gospel%20of%20Wellness%26quot%3B%20and%20of%20the%20newsletter%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwelltodo.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWell%20To%20Do%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20wellness%20industry.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20Peloton%20isn't%20a%20good%20business%20model%3B%20it's%20that%20it%20simply%20isn't%20a%20mass%20product%20but%20more%20of%20a%20niche%2C%20luxe%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20pulled%20forward%20a%20lot%20of%20demand%2C%20meaning%20people%20who%20would%20have%20considered%20buying%20Peloton%20equipment%20down%20the%20road%20decided%20to%20go%20ahead%20and%20pull%20the%20trigger%20in%202020.%20Much%20like%20other%20pandemic%20business%20darlings%2C%20Peloton%20thought%20the%20level%20of%20demand%20was%20a%20long-term%20shift%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20one-off%20event%2C%20so%20it%20invested%20accordingly.%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20by%20the%20time%20the%20company%20got%20its%20manufacturing%20and%20supply%20chain%20up%20to%20speed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-pelotons-supply-chain-fell-prey-to-the-bullwhip-effect-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20wasn't%20necessary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeloton%20saw%20their%20strength%20in%20COVID%20and%20ran%20it%20forward%20in%20perpetuity%2C%20and%20that%20simply%20is%20not%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20Simeon%20Siegel%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20BMO%20Capital%20Markets%20who%20covers%20Peloton%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeloton%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20cratering%20demand%2C%20the%20company%20has%20faced%20various%20headaches%20in%20recent%20years.%20It%20has%20issued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-recalls-more-than-2-millions-original-1400-bikes-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-will-pay-19-million-penalty-over-treadmill-incidents-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecalls%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20devices%20and%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-has-pulled-commercial-with-chris-noth-off-social-media-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic-relations%20debacles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20slashed%20staff%20and%20outsourced%20logistics%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20get%20on%20steadier%20financial%20footing.%20It%20now%20says%20it's%20trying%20to%20cut%20%24200%20million%20from%20its%20annual%20expenses%20by%20mid-2025%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20that%20will%20be%20enough.%20Investors%20have%20soured%20on%20the%20company%2C%20and%20Peloton's%20once%20%2450%20billion%20market%20cap%20has%20fallen%20to%20under%20%242%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20troubles%20don't%20necessarily%20mean%20all%20is%20lost.%20Siegel%20thinks%20Peloton%20is%20just%20too%20focused%20on%20growing%20instead%20of%20looking%20at%20its%20user%20base%20and%20squeezing%20cash%20out%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20primary%20focus%20should%20be%20on%20bear-hugging%20their%20brand%20loyalists%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20trying%20to%20find%20new%2C%20money-losing%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20business%20that%20convinces%20people%20to%20pay%20over%20%2440%20a%20month%20to%20get%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20equipment%20in%20their%20home.%20That's%20an%20incredibly%20profitable%20story%2C%20and%20yet%20the%20company%20loses%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fpeloton-stock-price-subscribers-loss-bike-seat-recall-consumer-spending-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeloton's%20subscriber%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20own%20isn't%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20everything%20else.%20The%20company%20has%20thin%20margins%20on%20hardware%2C%20as%20in%20selling%20bikes%20and%20treadmills%20and%20rowers%20and%20whatever%20else%2C%20but%20it%20has%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-prices-inflation-soaring-corporate-greed-profits-margins-wages-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobust%20margins%20on%20subscriptions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Paul%20Golding%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Macquarie%20Capital%2C%20said.%20Instead%20of%20spending%20on%20getting%20more%20bikes%20into%20people's%20homes%2C%20it%20could%20just%20keep%20its%20attention%20on%20discouraging%20people%20from%20unsubscribing.%20But%20it's%20not%20doing%20that%2C%20so%20other%20costs%20are%20eating%20into%20its%20subscription%20margins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20other%20expenses%20that%20the%20business%20incurs%2C%20including%20marketing%20expenses%2C%20general%20administrative%20expenses%2C%20and%20research%20and%20development%2C%20given%20that%20they%20are%20a%20tech%20platform%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Golding%20said.%20%26quot%3BOver%20the%20last%20few%20quarters%2C%20there's%20been%20stagnating%20expectations%20of%20connected-fitness%20subscribers%20as%20well%20as%20declines%20in%20the%20more%20entry-level%20app.%20Those%20economies%20of%20scale%20have%20not%20been%20working%20in%20favor%20of%20outpacing%20the%20cost%20structure%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20left%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20path%20ahead%20is%20rocky.%20Peloton%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeloton-treadmill-customers-threaten-class-action-lawsuit-over-treadmill-membership-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20decent%20subscriber%20base%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20more%20than%203%20million%20paid%20connected%20subscribers%20(meaning%20people%20who%20have%20the%20device%20and%20a%20subscription)%20and%20675%2C000%20paid%20app%20users%20(they%20didn't%20buy%20equipment%20and%20have%20the%20app%20only)%20at%20the%20end%20of%20its%20most%20recent%20quarter.%20But%20there%20is%20churn.%20It%20expects%20its%20subscriptions%20to%20fall%20in%20the%20current%20quarter%2C%20and%20its%20paid%20app%20use%20has%20been%20on%20the%20downslope.%20When%20I%20went%20to%20look%20up%20Peloton%20on%20Google%20Trends%20for%20this%20story%20over%20the%20past%20month%2C%20%26quot%3Bhow%20to%20cancel%20peloton%20subscription%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20second%20search%20listed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeloton%20has%20plenty%20of%20direct%20competitors%20in%20the%20connected-fitness-hardware%20space%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fechelon-fitness-increased-sales-700-percent-competing-with-peloton-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEchelon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftonal-review-home-fitness-startup-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETonal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20also%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20the%20gym%2C%20which%20has%20all%20sorts%20of%20classes%20and%20fitness%20equipment%20that%20let%20people%20mix%20things%20up%2C%20including%2C%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20Pelotons%20or%20other%20connected-fitness%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20get%20competing%20content%20and%20do%20it%20on%20demand%20at%20your%20gym%20and%20just%20pay%20the%20monthly%20membership%20fee%20of%20the%20gym%20and%20also%20be%20able%20to%20use%20a%20bunch%20of%20other%20things%20when%20you're%20not%20feeling%20a%20spin%20ride%20today%2C%20then%20does%20that%20change%20the%20value%20proposition%20for%20you%20when%20you're%20thinking%20about%20whether%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20buy%20a%20%242%2C000-plus%20piece%20of%20equipment%3F%26quot%3B%20Golding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F10-youtube-fitness-channels-for-home-workouts-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you're%20shy%20about%20working%20out%20in%20public%20and%20worried%20about%20spending%20cash%20on%20expensive%20gear%20or%20any%20sort%20of%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWant%20to%20work%20out%20from%20home%3F%26quot%3B%20Raphael%2C%20the%20wellness%20author%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%20just%20log%20on%20to%20YouTube%20for%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20issues%20specific%20to%20Peloton%2C%20the%20company%20faces%20an%20age-old%20reality%20of%20fitness%3A%20Trends%20come%20and%20go%20quickly%2C%20whether%20it%20be%20Jazzercise%2C%20Zumba%2C%20CrossFit%2C%20Pilates%2C%20Cardio%20Barre%2C%20or%2C%20well%2C%20you%20get%20the%20point.%20Fitness%20is%20a%20lot%20like%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20is%20a%20capitalist%2C%20consumerist%20nation%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20we%20experience%20fitness%20as%20a%20capitalist%2C%20consumer%20product.%20Yes%2C%20the%20science%20changes%20somewhat%20%E2%80%94%20we%20didn't%20really%20think%20cardio%20was%20for%20everyone%20until%20the%20'60s%20and%20'70s%2C%20or%20really%20push%20strength%20training%20until%20the%20'90s%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvintage-photos-exercise-trends