years%20and%20rent%20a%20condo%20in%20Austin.%20They%20want%20to%20hit%20financial%20goals%20before%20having%20kids.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Stinson%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-austin-want-make-350000-before-having-kids-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20are%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20%E2%80%94%20and%20college%20is%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20they're%20cutting%20from%20their%20budgets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Back%20of%20person%20with%20backpack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d1e87b4abc992e8c7a9f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMillennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20are%20cutting%20college%20from%20their%20budgets.%3Cp%3EFotoDuets%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20Deloitte%20survey%20found%20that%20a%20third%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20chose%20to%20skip%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20key%20reasons%20come%20down%20to%20cost%20and%20preference%20for%20careers%20that%20don't%20require%20degrees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20comes%20as%20over%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20are%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYounger%20workers%20are%20foregoing%20higher%20education%20as%20costs%20continue%20to%20remain%20top%20of%20mind%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-enrollment-crisis-what-is-causing-it-fafsa-student-debt-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evalue%20of%20a%20college%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20Deloitte%20released%20a%20survey%20on%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20attitudes%20toward%20the%20world%20and%20their%20financial%20conditions.%20Using%20responses%20from%2014%2C468%20Gen%20Z%20and%208%2C373%20millennials%20across%2044%20countries%2C%20the%20survey%20found%20that%20a%20third%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20chose%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-value-of-college-higher-education-student-debt-tuition-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforego%20higher%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20primary%20reasons%20being%20financial%20barriers%2C%20family%20or%20personal%20circumstances%2C%20and%20seeking%20careers%20that%20don't%20require%20college%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCost%20of%20living%20is%20their%20top%20societal%20concern.%20The%20financial%20constraints%20of%20higher%20education%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20number%20one%20reason%20that%20Gen%20Zs%20and%20millennials%20are%20not%20pursuing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Deloitte%20Global%20Chief%20People%20%26amp%3B%20Purpose%20Officer%20Elizabeth%20Faber%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20comes%20as%20over%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20are%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20per%20the%20report%20%E2%80%94%20a%20continued%20trend%20among%20younger%20workers.%20For%20both%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20their%20top%20concern%2C%20with%20Gen%20Z%20also%20concerned%20about%20potential%20unemployment.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20both%20generations%20reported%20that%20they%20don't%20feel%20financially%20secure.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20many%20might%20be%20seeking%20out%20careers%20that%20bring%20stability%20and%20don't%20necessarily%20require%20a%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20looking%20for%20roles%20that%20are%20making%20them%20less%20prone%20for%20disruption%2C%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20automation%2C%26quot%3B%20Faber%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20trend%20that's%20been%20gaining%20more%20prominence%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstories-of-student-loan-debt-hamster-wheel-borrowers-cant-escape-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudent%20debt%20loads%20remain%20high%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20more%20jobs%20become%20available%20that%20do%20not%20require%20degrees%2C%20more%20Gen%20Z%20are%20deciding%20that%20college%20just%20isn't%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-value-of-college-higher-education-student-debt-tuition-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20July%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20YouGov%2C%20found%20that%20just%2039%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20said%20advancing%20their%20education%20was%20important%20to%20them%2C%20and%2046%25%20of%20them%20did%20not%20think%20going%20to%20college%20was%20worth%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2022-year-old%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-value-of-college-higher-education-student-debt-tuition-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20decided%20to%20drop%20out%20of%20college%20after%20just%20a%20few%20months%20because%20she%20saw%20that%20the%20business%20courses%20she%20was%20paying%20for%20were%20topics%20she%20could%20teach%20herself%2C%20and%20she%20hasn't%20looked%20back%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20amazing%20for%20me%20to%20not%20be%20in%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20student%20loans%2C%20like%20so%20many%20of%20my%20friends%20are%20in%20%24100%2C000%20in%20debt%20and%20student%20loans%20just%20to%20get%20a%20job%20that%20pays%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20younger%20adults'%20perceptions%20toward%20higher%20education%20seem%20to%20skew%20away%20from%20overall%20attitudes%20toward%20a%20postsecondary%20degree%20or%20credential.%20A%20new%20report%20from%20Gallup%20and%20the%20Lumina%20Foundation%20on%20the%20state%20of%20higher%20education%20in%202024%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Badults'%20interest%20in%20pursuing%20some%20form%20of%20higher%20education%20is%20at%20the%20highest%20level%26quot%3B%20the%20organizations%20have%20ever%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20which%20used%20a%20sample%20of%20over%2014%2C000%20adults%20who%20are%20either%20enrolled%20in%20a%20postsecondary%20program%2C%20were%20previously%20enrolled%20but%20had%20not%20completed%20a%20degree%2C%20or%20have%20never%20enrolled%20in%20a%20program%2C%20nearly%20all%20adults%20without%20a%20college%20degree%20say%20that%20having%20at%20least%20one%20type%20of%20credential%20is%20%26quot%3Bextremely%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bvery%26quot%3B%20valuable.%20Of%20course%2C%20cost%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20main%20barriers%20to%20obtaining%20that%20degree%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20higher%20education%20can%20be%20important%20for%20workers%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0both%20in%20their%20careers%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20learn.%20Deloitte%20found%2C%20per%20Faber%2C%20that%20the%20types%20of%20jobs%20held%20by%20respondents%20with%20higher%20levels%20of%20education%20tend%20to%20provide%20longer-term%20job%20security%3B%20those%20respondents%20are%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20secondary%20sources%20of%20income.%20Women%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20than%20men%20to%20cite%20financial%20constraints%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20not%20pursuing%20higher%20education%2C%20even%20though%20they're%20less%20likely%20to%20lack%20interest%20in%20getting%20one%2C%20per%20Faber.%20That%20potentially%20points%20to%20continued%20inequities%2C%20especially%20as%20workers%20with%20higher%20education%20feel%20more%20confident%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20retire%20comfortably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20a%20higher%20education%20might%20have%20its%20own%20trickle-down%20effect%20on%20daily%20work%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26qu