D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-away-big-city-bad-career-job-market-suburbs-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecareer%20trap%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20layoffs%20loom%2C%20and%20AI%20robots%20circle%20like%20vultures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeOliveira%20said%20that%20outside%20Boston%2C%20where%20she%20grew%20up%2C%20the%20thinking%20was%20if%20you%20do%20blue-collar%20work%2C%20%26quot%3Byou're%20not%20as%20smart%20as%20someone%20who%20went%20to%20college%2C%20you're%20not%20as%20dedicated.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20blue-collar%20work%20is%20an%20oasis%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bustle.com%2Flife%2Ffake-email-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efake-email-job%20desert%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20a%20newfound%20social%20cachet.%20%26quot%3BFor%20my%20family%2C%20they%20look%20at%20it%20differently%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20tell%20my%20cousins%20that%20are%20still%20in%20school%2C%20look%20into%20the%20trades%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20America%2C%20it's%20getting%20hot%20under%20the%20blue%20collar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Collins%20has%20been%20a%20plumber%20for%20two%20decades.%20After%20finishing%20high%20school%2C%20he%20moved%20to%20eastern%20Tennessee%20in%20search%20of%20pretty%20much%20any%20type%20of%20work.%20But%20with%20no%20college%20degree%20and%20visible%20tattoos%20dotting%20his%20arms%2C%20he%20found%20that%20prospective%20employers%20sidelined%20him.%20Then%20he%20heard%20about%20a%20plumber%20looking%20for%20help.%20He%20showed%20up%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20is%20pipe-fixing%20history%3A%20He%20got%20trained%2C%20got%20licensed%2C%20and%2C%20in%202008%2C%20struck%20out%20on%20his%20own.%20Business%2C%20he%20said%2C%20never%20skipped%20a%20beat%2C%20even%20when%20the%20market%20crashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20telling%20my%20parents%20that%20I%20was%20getting%20into%20the%20trades%2C%20and%20they%20were%20just%20like%3A%20'This%20is%20awful.%20Go%20to%20college%2C%20go%20to%20college%2C%20be%20an%20IT%20guy%20or%20a%20doctor%2C'%26quot%3B%20Collins%20told%20me.%20He%20believes%20they%20wanted%20more%20for%20him.%20But%20as%20they%20watched%20his%20career%20take%20off%2C%20they%20came%20to%20understand%20that%20plumbing%20did%20offer%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollins%20traced%20the%20shift%20around%20blue-collar%20work%20back%20to%202018%20or%202019%2C%20when%20social%20media%20became%20a%20way%20for%20people%20to%20peek%20behind%20the%20trades%20curtain.%20As%20Steven%20Kurutz%20wrote%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F28%2Fstyle%2Ftiktoks-finest-lobsterman.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20early%20influencers%20focused%20on%20curating%20the%20most%20aesthetically%20pleasing%20lives%20possible.%20Then%20people%20began%20to%20wonder%20who%20crafted%20that%20pretty%20finery.%20Who%20catches%20the%20lobster%20that%20ends%20up%20on%20that%20hand-painted%20porcelain%20platter%3F%20Who%20builds%20that%20cavernous%20house%20packed%20with%20Eames%20chairs%3F%20As%20the%20wild%20popularity%20of%20%26quot%3Bday%20in%20the%20life%26quot%3B%20vignettes%20made%20clear%2C%20people%20loved%20what%20that%20peek%20afforded.%20If%20Instagram%20incentivized%20a%20still-life%20aesthetic%20pleasure%20neatly%20tucked%20into%20a%20square%20frame%2C%20TikTok%20incentivized%20action%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20people%20who%20spend%20their%20lives%20moving%20or%20building%20things%20were%20rewarded%20with%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20millennials%20and%20younger%20workers%20wrestled%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FSLOAS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esnowballing%20amount%20of%20student-loan%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20degrees%20that%20didn't%20seem%20worth%20the%20price%20tag.%20The%20median%20wage%