e%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20that%20there's%20been%20stigma%20and%20a%20general%20sense%20that%20these%20kinds%20of%20industries%20and%20this%20kind%20of%20work%20is%20somehow%20less%20than%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Pillar%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Jobber%2C%20a%20software%20company%20that%20services%20small%20blue-collar%20businesses%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BObviously%20we%20think%20that's%20total%20horseshit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Goldalian%2C%20an%20electrician%20who%20owns%20two%20brick-and-mortar%20stores%20and%20runs%20a%20YouTube%20channel%20that%20teaches%20people%20how%20to%20become%20electrical%20contractors%2C%20believes%20that%20just%20posting%20about%20the%20merits%20of%20blue-collar%20jobs%20might%20elide%20the%20hard%20work%20required%20to%20make%20it%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20dark%20side%20to%20the%20trades%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAs%20an%20electrician%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20get%20proper%20training%2C%20where%20to%20get%20training%20or%20licensing%2C%20you're%20setting%20yourself%20up%20for%20failure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlue-collar%20work%20is%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20work.%20There%20are%20bad%20bosses%2C%20difficult%20coworkers%2C%20and%20shareholders%20who%20value%20their%20profits%20over%20the%20workers%20generating%20them.%20Americans%20increasingly%20want%20more%20from%20their%20work%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20leverage%20to%20truly%20change%20their%20conditions%20%E2%80%94%20yet.%20The%20appeal%20of%20blue-collar%20work%20might%20lie%20in%20the%20fact%20that%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20it%20satisfies%20the%20conditions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwrong-great-resignation-recession-means-workers-powerless-despite-labor-shortage-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomists%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20required%20for%20worker%20power%3A%20Employers%20need%20this%20wo