C%20affecting%20the%20lives%20of%20many%20immigrant%20workers%20on%20H-1B%20visas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20USCIS%20guidelines%20outline%20various%20avenues%20for%20these%20individuals%2C%20offering%20a%20chance%20to%20extend%20their%20stay.%20So%20what%20are%20the%20options%20beyond%20the%2060-day%20grace%20period%20for%20someone%20on%20H-1B%20visa%20who%20has%20lost%20their%20job%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFile%20for%20a%20change%20of%20nonimmigrant%20status%20within%20the%20grace%20period%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFile%20an%20adjustment%20of%20status%20application%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFile%20an%20application%20for%20%26quot%3Bcompelling%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20under%20which%20workers%20may%20qualify%20for%20a%20one-year%20Employment%20Authorisation%20Document%20(EAD).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFile%20an%20application%20to%20become%20beneficiary%20of%20a%20nonfrivolous%20petition%20to%20change%20employer%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20USCIS%20says%20the%20concept%20of%20portability%2C%20enables%20eligible%20H-1B%20nonimmigrants%20to%20transition%20smoothly%20to%20new%20employment%20opportunities.%20This%20flexibility%20allows%20individuals%20to%20begin%20work%20with%20a%20new%20employer%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20nonfrivolous%20H-1B%20petition%20is%20filed%2C%20without%20waiting%20for%20its%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorkers%20who%20are%20eligible%20to%20apply%20for%20immigrant%20visas%20through%20self-petitioning%20can%20submit%20their%20petitions%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20they%20apply%20to%20adjust%20their%20status.%20While%20their%20adjustment%20applications%20are%20being%20processed%2C%20these%20workers%20can%20stay%20in%20the%20U.S.%20and%20acquire%20an%20Employment%20Authorization%20Document%20(EAD).%20In%20cases%20where%20individuals%20have%20been%20granted%20immigrant%20visa%20petitions%20based%20on%20employment%20and%20are%20facing%20significant%20challenges%2C%20they%20may%20be%20eligible%20for%20a%20one-year%20